description.narrative: (Uzbekistan): The Regional Community Connections program complements existing assistance programs in Uzbekistan by providing support to improve infectious diseases diagnosis and treatment to improve the quality and efficiency of healthcare services. ~Exchange programs are an effective cross-cutting tool that transfers new skills and knowledge and builds the professional capacity of local leaders. ~FY 2014 health funds will focus on~improving access to quality healthcare and supporting the enabling environment~for the expansion and improvement of TB services in Uzbekistan. ~The knowledge and skills obtained will be applied in strategic planning for introduction of a reliable TB surveillance and prevention system and for adjusting national TB policies.
